page_1_img_1.png.description: Left diagram shows a beam of length l with roller support at left end and fixed support at right end, subjected to uniformly distributed upward load q along its length. Coordinate system shows y-axis vertical, x and z axes horizontal. Right diagram displays a rectangular cross-section labeled "SECT A-A" with dimensions a × a, showing two regions labeled E₁ and E₂ with diagonal hatching patterns indicating different material properties or stress distributions.

page_1_img_2.png.description: Cantilever beam with fixed support (hatched) at left end and free right end. Beam length l with vertical spring support of stiffness k shown at the free end (indicated by zigzag spring symbol and ground symbol). Labels show EI_xx, GA indicating bending stiffness and shear rigidity properties. Vertical force F shown with upward arrow at right end.

page_2_img_1.png.description: Two-member frame structure with horizontal member A-B and inclined member B-C. Point A has fixed support (hatched), point B has roller support on ground (circles with hatching), and distributed load q₂ acts along inclined member B-C shown by arrows. Coordinate system shows y-axis vertical and x-axis horizontal. Points labeled A, B, and C with angle indicators at joints.

page_2_img_2.png.description: Three-dimensional isometric view of semi-monocoque beam structure showing four longitudinal stringers (bold lines) at corners of rectangular cross-section with dimension a × a. Multiple cross-sections of length l shown with distributed loads (upward arrows) applied to top surface and side surfaces. Points A and B marked on stringers, with dotted lines indicating internal structure. Coordinate system shows length l along beam axis. Structure appears to represent a box beam with skin panels and corner stringers subjected to aerodynamic or pressure loading.

page_3_img_1.png.description: Beam with fixed supports (hatched) at both ends, total length l divided into two equal segments l/2. Applied moment M_x shown at midspan with curved arrow indicating clockwise rotation. Label EI_ax indicates axial bending stiffness. Horizontal dimension arrows show beam subdivided into l/2 and l/2 segments.

page_3_img_2.png.description: Simple beam of length l with two point masses (shown as filled circles) labeled as points 1 and 2. Coordinate system shows y-axis vertical, x-axis horizontal, and ξ (xi) axis vertical on right side. Points are positioned symmetrically along the beam length. Diagram appears to represent a discrete mass system or lumped mass model for dynamic analysis.
